<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Education Minister Returns From Visit to Romania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Education Minister Returns From Visit to Romania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2004140294 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2004140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] National Education Minister Nevzat Ayaz, who 
concluded his official visit to Romania, returned to Turkey this 
evening. In a statement at Istanbul's Ataturk Airport, Ayaz 
said that a three-year education protocol was signed between 
Turkey and Romania. Under the protocol, the two countries will 
exchange educational and cultural programs, Ayaz noted. 
Pointing out that a decision was also made to develop joint 
projects in the educational field, Ayaz reported that the 
exchange of staff members between the two countries' 
universities was also discussed during the talks in Romania. 
Ayaz said that he also met with the Romanian president and 
discussed bilateral relations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

