<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bomb Blast Causes `Serious' Damage </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Blast Causes `Serious' Damage </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2204055594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0400 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2204055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The antiterrorism unit believes that the explosion 
of a powerful home-made time bomb that ignited at 2330 [2030 
GMT] last night under a car was the work of 17 November and ELA 
[Revolutionary People's Struggle], or of ELA. The car, which 
was parked at the intersection of Rigas Fereos and Mesoyion 
Streets in the vicinity of the Pentagon [Greek National Defense 
General Staff headquarters], belongs to the Mille company. The 
explosion caused serious material damage to shops and buildings 
in the area. 

</TEXT>

