<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Stresses Strong Ties With Germany </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Stresses Strong Ties With Germany </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2004170794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1525 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2004170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 20 (AA) -- The Foreign Ministry on 
Wednesday [20 April] said that relations between Turkey and 
Germany have very strong foundations, adding neither country 
should allow third countries or circles to hurt them. 
  Speaking at his weekly briefing on Wednesday, he said that 
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has personally confirmed 
the fact that German tanks were not used by Turkey in its 
operations carried out against terrorists. 
  He said that from time to time misunderstandings can emerge 
between two countries, which in turn lead to certain 
difficulties. 
  "What matters is that both countries should be determined to 
overcome them," Ataman said. "Both countries have the necessary 
political will for this. Turkey hopes the strengthening of 
existing mutual trust will help to overcome these 
misunderstandings." 

</TEXT>

