<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Papandreou Begins U.S. Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Papandreou Begins U.S. Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Clinton `Warm Toward Greece, Papandreou' </H4>

<F P=102> NC2204112994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0900 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2204112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The meeting between Greek Prime Minister Andreas 
Papandreou and U.S. President Bill Clinton this evening at the 
White House is anticipated with great interest. Our 
correspondent in Washington Mirella Kalostipi reported that the 
two leaders will discuss the situation in the Balkans, the 
problem between Athens and Skopje, the Bosnian crisis, the 
Cyprus issue, the tension in Greek-Turkish and Greek-Albanian 
relations and also the further improvement of relations between 
Greece and United States. 
  It should be noted that while addressing Prime Minister 
Papandreou last night at the reception in his honor, the U.S. 
President appeared particularly warm toward Greece and 
Papandreou, and expressed the certainty that their talks would 
be successful. 

</TEXT>

