<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "`PARIS MATCH -- BVA Opinion Poll: </F>
The Fall of Prime Minister Balladur (Down 9 Percent)"] 
  [Text] The latest "PARIS MATCH -- BVA" opinion poll, 
conducted after the withdrawal of the CIP [youth job training 
contract] but before the suicide of [President's Mitterrand's 
adviser] Francois de Grossouvre, shows a real drop in Edouard 
Balladur's popularity. He has lost 9 percent, posting his worst 
score since he took office. His popularity rating is negative 
for the first time and is now below that of Francois Mitterrand. 
It should be noted that the prime minister's rating has dropped 
considerably (down 15 percent), compared with people with more 
centrist views. The government as a whole has been affected by 
this fall from grace since, also for the first time, the French 
people -- if they were deputies -- would not support the 
government in a confidence vote (49 percent no's as opposed to 
39 percent yes-votes). As a result of this situation, the Left 
has gained 3 percent in legislative election voting intentions. 
The Left-Right balance of power is now 34-44. 


