  This survey was conducted in a series of one-on-one 
interviews with a representative sample of the French population 
over age 18. The questions for the ratings poll were put to 928 
people between 31 March and 6 April 1994, while 3,747 people 
were asked their general election voting intentions between 15 
March and 18 March 1994, and between 31 March and 6 April 1994. 
Voting intentions were calculated on the basis of people listed 
on the electoral registers. Sampling was done using the quota 
method: sex, age, profession of the head of the household, 
region, and category of town. The results should be seen in the 
light of a margin of error common to all opinion polls and 
related to the size of the sample. These margins of error are: 
more or less one or two points for voting intentions; more or 
less two or three points for overall results; and more or less 
four or five points for the results for the major political 
groups. 

