<F P=102>   BR2204120994 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database in French 0702 GMT 22 
Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2204120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA Database </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed BN/AZ: "A Hundred Swiss Observers in South </F>
Africa -- Good Offices Mission for the First Multiracial 
Elections"] 
  [Excerpts] Bern, 22 Apr (ATS) -- The dispatch of 100 
observers to monitor the election process in South Africa is 
part of Switzerland's good offices policy. This will be the 
27th mission of this kind since 1989, involving the largest 
number of participants and being the most expensive of all. 
[passage omitted] 
  With 100 observers, the Swiss team is the biggest national 
contingent within the UN observation mission in South Africa. 
The cost of the operation is estimated at 1.5 million Swiss 
francs. 

</TEXT>

