BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Patrick Jarreau on "SOFRES" poll conducted for LE </F>
MONDE and RTL] 
  [Excerpts] One year after taking office, the Balladur 
government is still judged relatively favorably by the French: 
32 percent give it a higher rating that its Socialist 
predecessor, which is favored by only 23 percent. However, 
one-third of those questioned (and almost one-half of them if 
the "no opinions" are added) cannot decide or preferred not to 
speak out in favor of either government. [passage omitted] 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
