  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Government supports U.S. 
President Bill Clinton's attitude in seeking to follow a tougher 
course in Bosnia. On Thursday [21 April], Government Spokesman 
Dieter Vogel stated in Bonn that the continuing aggression by 
Serbian combat troops and their political leaders' constantly 
broken promises grossly violate the basic rules of humanity and 
international law. 
  The military and economic countermeasures mentioned by 
Clinton are part of the options of the allies to bring the 
Bosnian-Serb leadership to its senses. The Federal Government 
calls for close political coordination between the European 
Union, NATO, the United Nations, the United States, and Russia. 
The Federal Government particularly welcomes the intention 
expressed by Clinton for political coordination, above all with 
Russia, to prepare further steps. This is the basic condition 
for clear and consistent action against the forces of 
aggression, Vogel stated. 

