  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Government will again 
help India with aid programs worth approximately 350 million 
German marks [DM], concentrating in particular on combating 
poverty and on environmental protection. This was announced by 
the Development Ministry on Thursday [21 April]. 
  After the conclusion of a round of negotiations in Bonn, 
DM315 million was promised in financial cooperation and DM36.5 
million in technical cooperation. The main targets are small 
industries, private business initiatives, and the elimination of 
bottlenecks in the energy supply. As examples the ministry 
cited a brown coal power plant, a factory for converting tree 
stumps into particle board, drinking water supply facilities, 
and the promotion of solar- energy centers. 

