<H3> <TI>   CDU, FDP Experts Advocate Volunteer Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CDU, FDP Experts Advocate Volunteer Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2004085094 Hamburg DPA in German 2304 GMT 19 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2004085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DPA) -- The criticism of FRG Defense 
Minister Volker Ruehe, Christian Democratic Union [CDU], and his 
Bundeswehr planning continues. In the BERLINER ZEITUNG 
(Wednesday [20 April] edition), defense experts of CDU and Free 
Democratic Party of Germany [FDP] called for the abolition of 
compulsory military service. 
  CDU politician Otto Hauser called for general compulsory 
service for men. In the future, there should be a free choice 
between military service or national alternative service, 
between police and fire brigade, disaster relief and 
environmental service. "Compulsory military service is 
outdated." Anyone who further reduces the Bundeswehr departs 
from the concept of compulsory military service, the defense 
expert said, referring to plans to reduce the Bundeswehr to 
320,000 men. Referring to Ruehe, the CDU politicians said: "I 
have never seen such behavior by a defense minister." One 
cannot push such profound changes in the armed forces through 
parliament in a "mad dash." He thinks the course that has been 
set is substantively wrong. Anyone who serves in the military 
for 10 months is effectively available for only eight months. 
  FDP Politician Juergen Koppelin said that he favors general 
compulsory service for men and women. There is no way to avoid 
an army of volunteers if compulsory military service is 
shortened further. One can hardly find words to describe the 
defense minister's confusion, criticized the FDP politician. 
"Mr. Ruehe finally must present a concept instead of constantly 
manipulating the figures." Compulsory military service of 10 
months would throw the Bundeswehr into organizational chaos. 

</TEXT>

