<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "People's Party for Freedom and </F>
Democracy Leader Bolkestein Wants To Be Prime Minister"] 
  [Text] It seems after all that VVD [People's Party for 
Freedom and Democracy] leader Bolkestein is ready to take on the 
job of prime minister if the liberals are the largest party 
following the elections. 
  Bolkestein believes that the political leader of a party 
must 
not shirk the responsibility of leading a government. 
  Four days ago, Bolkestein stated that he attached more 
importance to membership in the Chamber than holding ministerial 
or prime ministerial office. 
  At a meeting in Alphen aan den Rijn, he stated yesterday 
evening that the VVD would not be bringing "any issues that can 
not be negotiated" into the formation of a new government. The 
VVD is seeking cutbacks of 17 billion guilders during the next 
term of government. If it is less than 15 billion, Bolkestein 
states that the VVD would withdraw its support. 

</TEXT>

