<F P=106> [Report signed K.V.: "Brinkman Down, Deetman Up"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Things are going well for [Second Chamber 
Speaker] Wim Deetman. As things get worse for Elco Brinkman 
[Christian Democratic Appeal (CDA) leader], the Chamber 
speaker's star is shining brighter. Rumors in The Hague suggest 
that he may soon become floor leader of the CDA or even end up 
as prime minister. 
  Until recently, Deetman responded to such speculation with 
declarations of love for his present job of Chamber speaker. 
This has changed two weeks before the elections. Last weekend 
he declared that "I will not run away from my responsibilities" 
if the party gives him the job of floor leader. In this week's 
VRIJ NEDERLAND, he did not even shy away from the high office of 
prime minister. As a good CDA man, he said that this would 
depend on consultations with the "home front," i.e., his wife 
and children. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

