<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reports Rapid Rise in Unemployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2204115294 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 21 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BR2204115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Unemployment Rising Faster Than </F>
Ever To Over 500,000"] 
  [Text] Unemployment is rising faster than ever before, with 
18,000 jobs lost every month. Such a rate of increase is the 
highest since the war. 
  This is clear from the latest unemployment figures published 
by the CBS [Central Statistics Office]. It is also the first 
time that unemployment has topped the half million mark since 
early 1986. 
  In an initial reaction to the figures, Social Affairs 
Minister De Vries spoke of an "alarming growth." "Strictly 
speaking, we are now facing an increase of 200,000 a year. It 
is clear that although there is already some prospect of 
economic recovery, the process of reducing jobs is still 
continuing steadily and the end is not yet in sight," the 
minister said. 
  De Vries believes that the new unemployment figures stress 
the need to lighten the costs burden on companies and for a more 
flexible labor market. "Also, employers and employees should 
exercise the greatest constraint not only in the current round 
of wage negotiations for this year, but also for 1995," De 
Vries stated. 

</TEXT>

