<H3> <TI>   Major Pays Tribute to Nixon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Major Pays Tribute to Nixon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304174894 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1722 GMT 23 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304174894 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Prime Minister today paid tribute to the role 
that the Richard Nixon played in ending the Cold War between 
East and West. 
  In a message to President Bill Clinton, John Major said he 
had heard "with sadness" the news of the former president's 
death. "I send to you and to the American people my sympathy 
and condolences," he said. 
  "Richard Nixon will be remembered for his tireless work for 
a 
better understanding between East and West. He was a leading 
architect of the process which led to the end of the Cold War 
and his judgment on international affairs was widely respected. 
He will be greatly missed by his many friends and admirers on 
this side of the Atlantic." 
  Contents of the message were released by the Foreign Office. 

