<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Steel Industry in West Reaches Wage Deal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Steel Industry in West Reaches Wage Deal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304123994 Berlin N-TV in German 1000 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin N-TV </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The steel sector wage dispute for the areas of North 
Rhine-Westphalia, Lower Saxony, and Bremen has been settled. 
The engineering union IG Metall and the employers have 
concluded an agreement aimed at safeguarding jobs. For the 
120,000 workers in this sector, they agreed that the 35-hour 
week will be brought forward from 1 April 1995 to 1 May 1994. 
For the first time, the union did not ask for a wage increase. 
The wage agreement will apply for 12 months. 

</TEXT>

