<H3> <TI>   National Alliance Concurs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Alliance Concurs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304113894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1045 GMT 
23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] A National Alliance-Italian Social Movement 
delegation led by Gianfranco Fini told the president that Forza 
Italia leader Silvio Berlusconi should head the next government. 
Fini hoped that Berlusconi would not invoke Article 92 of the 
Constitution and independently choose his ministerial team. He 
added that if Berlusconi were asked to form the government he 
would be able to offer complete guarantees for avoiding a 
conflict of interest, perhaps via a guarantor. Fini said he was 
sure that the government would have the Senate's confidence. 
[passage omitted] 

