<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nationals Ignore Advice, Remain in Serbia, Montenegro </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nationals Ignore Advice, Remain in Serbia, Montenegro </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304202494 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2304202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid TVE Internacional Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Several Western embassies have decided to evacuate 
their nationals from Serbia and Montenegro (Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia) as a precaution against Serb positions in Gorazde 
being bombed in the next few hours and the possibility of 
reprisals. The United States, Great Britain, and France, whose 
aircraft could take part directly in the bombing, have already 
started the evacuation of Belgrade. As for the families of the 
diplomatic staff and employees of the Spanish mission in 
Belgrade -- a total of about 16 people -- only four of them have 
decided to leave the country, following the advice of the 
Spanish Government. As for the Spanish population of Serbia and 
Montenegro -- according to diplomatic sources, about 50 people, 
mostly the wives or children of Serbs -- they have said that 
they do not feel threatened at present and are not considering 
evacuation. 

</TEXT>

