<DOCNO> FBIS4-19873 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu079_n_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-079 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  24 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   Search for Foreign Submarines Proves Fruitless </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Search for Foreign Submarines Proves Fruitless </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2404164894 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1545 GMT 24 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2404164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Navy's search for foreign submarines in the 
waters off Norrkoeping has not led to any results, but according 
to the defense staff there are several indications of alien 
underwater activity. The military have not completed their 
analyses yet, but according to some reports, the analyses 
concern mainly propeller noise. The submarine search force, 
which has been practicing in the archipelago off Norrkoeping for 
some time, will remain in the area for a few more days. 

</TEXT>

