<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Cites Turkish Obstacles to CBM's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis Cites Turkish Obstacles to CBM's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2404193794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek GMT 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2404193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis said that it is not 
only the question of access to Famagusta which constitutes an 
obstacle to agreement on implementing the confidence-building 
measures [CBM's]. There is a series of other questions, he 
noted, which the Turkish side keeps putting forward and which, 
if accepted, would lead to the pseudostate's recognition. 
President Kliridhis made this statement to journalists who 
visited him to greet him on his birthday today. 
  The president added that the Turks do not agree for 
Famagusta 
and the International Nicosia Airport to be placed under UN 
administration. The Turks, he added, insist that there must be 
a co-administration, not UN administration. 

</TEXT>

