<H3> <TI>   Turkish Delegation Concludes Contacts, Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Delegation Concludes Contacts, Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404140194 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 10300 GMT 24 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkish State Minister Mehmet Ali Yilmaz concluded 
his contacts in the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus [TRNC] 
and left the island today. 
  Speaking at a news conference before his departure at Ercan 
State Airport, Yilmaz said that during his stay he visited the 
investment projects in the TRNC and was briefed on them. He 
noted that the investments that continued in 1994 will be 
concluded in accordance with a time table. Pointing out that 
the greatest problem of the TRNC is the budget deficit, Yilmaz 
added that the Turkish government will try and solve this 
problem. He concluded by expressing his satisfaction over this 
first visit to the TRNC. 
  Prime Minister Hakki Atun said that Yilmaz's visit gave them 
the opportunity to brief the Turkish minister on the investments 
being made, adding that Turkish delegation was informed on the 
problems of the coalition government. He noted that the talks 
between Turkey and the TRNC were beneficial and that the Turkish 
side had a sincere approach to the problems of the Turkish 
cypriots. Atun concluded by thanking the delegation for their 
approach. 
  Atun, Deputy Prime Minister Ozker Ozgur, Turkish Ambassador 
to Lefkosa [Nicosia] Cahit Bayar, commander of the security 
forces, president of the supreme court, various ministers and 
other officials were present at the airport ceremony. 

</TEXT>

