<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Asks To Revert to Original Version of CBM's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas Asks To Revert to Original Version of CBM's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2404140294 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1030 GMT 24 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2404140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Rauf Denktas has stressed that the 
confidence-building measures [CBM] package must be reversed to 
its original form. Mehmet Ali Yilmaz, Turkish state minister in 
charge of Cyprus affairs, paid a farewell visit on Denktas this 
morning. 
  Replying to reporters' questions after the meeting, Denktas 
said that there are promises made in the first version of the 
CBM package and recalled that Greek Cypriot leader Glavkos 
Kliridhis accepted the package before it was changed. 
Explaining that the package was eliminated as a result of 
negotiations conducted subsequently, Denktas noted that 
Kliridhis acted as if he accepted the package although he 
actually had not. This was Kliridhis' tactics, Denktas remarked. 
  Denktas declared that the original package must be 
reinstated, adding that work can be conducted on this version. 

</TEXT>

