<F P=103> NC2504073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] A few minutes ago National Economy Finance 
Minister Yeoryios Yennimatas died in the intensive care unit at 
Evangelismos Hospital. He was born in Athens in 1939. [passage 
omitted] 
  Yennimatas personally told the Greek people that he was 
suffering from cancer. He went to the United States for 
treatment and after a few weeks returned to Athens with obvious 
hope that he had surpassed the danger. His condition 
deteriorated and again he informed the people, this time telling 
them that the cancer had affected his liver. His wife, Kakia, 
died of cancer a few months ago. 

