<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Acarkan Continues Visit, Meets Party Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Acarkan Continues Visit, Meets Party Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2304185794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2304185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Ayhan Halit Acarkan, speaker of the Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus who is on an official visit in 
Ankara, and his accompanying delegation have been continuing 
their contacts. The guest speaker visited the leaders of the 
political parties at the parliament and exchanged views. 
  Acarkan first visited the Republican People's Party leader 
Deniz Baykal. Later, he visited the Nationalist Action Party 
leader Alpaslan Turkes and communicated to him that the Turkish 
Cypriots supported continuing with the negotiations however, he 
added, the confidence-building measures were in favor of the 
Greek Cypriots. Turkes, in turn, said that the Cyprus issue is 
costing the Turkish nation, but notwithstanding the Turkish 
nation, nobody can give concessions on the Cyprus issue. 
  Subsequently, Acarkan and his delegation visited Democratic 
Left Party leader Bulent Ecevit. Ecevit stated that it is 
incomprehensible that those who are not intervening in the 
cruelty in Bosnia-Herzegovina are intervening in the peace in 
Cyprus. 
  Lastly, Acarkan and his delegation visited the Prosperity 
Party leader Necmettin Erbakan. Erbakan stated they do not 
recognize an issue such as Cyprus, that peace was established in 
the island in 1974, and that the issue was resolved then. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

