<H3> <TI>   Golhan Returns From Russia, Comments on Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Golhan Returns From Russia, Comments on Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2504080894 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2504080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] National Defense Minister Mehmet Golhan has 
returned home after concluding his visit to the Russian 
Federation. 
  In a statement at Ankara's Esenboga Airport, Golhan said 
that 
the defense industry cooperation agreement signed in Moscow 
envisages an initial purchase of 42 armored vehicles and 
urgently required ammunition. Golhan noted that experts are 
working on the purchase of two helicopters, which will serve a 
mobile hospital 
  Stating that Turkey attaches great importance to 
good-neighborly relations and cooperation, Golhan stated that as 
the free market economy in Russia develops, its relations with 
Turkey will be strengthened in all areas. 
  Pointing out that the clashes in the Caucasus were 
emphasized 
during meetings with Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev, 
Golhan added that finding solutions to regional issues under the 
umbrella of the United Nations was also assessed. 
  Stating that during his talks, the idea of converting the 
Black Sea into a sea of friendship was enhanced, Golhan 
expressed the hope that this spirit of friendship and 
cooperation will spread to other neighbors and enable all 
regional countries to live in peace and tranquillity. 

</TEXT>

