<F P=103> NC2204170394 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul MILLIYET </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The renowned Jirki, Gevdan, Mamguran, Giravi, and 
Goran tribes in Sirnak and Hakkari Provinces have joined their 
forces against the Workers Party of Kurdistan [PKK]. The 
tribes, which have thousands of armed men, assembled in 
Beytussebap District to demonstrate against the PKK at 1030 
yesterday. Some 5,000 demonstrators marched and chanted: "The 
banner will not be lowered; the cause cannot be abandoned; the 
Turkish, Kurdish, Laz [Black Sea people], and Circassian peoples 
are brothers; this country will be the PKK's grave; the PKK will 
drown in the blood it sheds." 

