<H3> <TI>   Germany, Netherlands Establish Military Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Germany, Netherlands Establish Military Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104114394 Hamburg DPA in German 0945 GMT 21 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2104114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The German-Dutch Corps will be 
established in The Hague on Friday [22 April] as the first joint 
military unit of the two countries. Defense Minister Volker 
Ruehe (Christian Democratic Union) and his Dutch counterpart 
Relus ter Beek will sign the agreement, the FRG Defense Ministry 
announced on Thursday [21 April] in Bonn. The corps will 
probably comprise between 50,000 and 70,000 soldiers. 
  The corps will be commanded by a joint corps staff in 
Muenster. Full combat readiness is to be reached in 1995. The 
first commander will be Dutch Major General Ruurd Reitsma. The 
first such unit to be established was the German-French corps, 
which was later supplemented by Belgian units. 

</TEXT>

