<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Welcomes NATO Ultimatum on Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Welcomes NATO Ultimatum on Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2304102894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0916 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2304102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel (FDP) [Free Democratic Party] welcomes the NATO ultimatum 
to the besiegers of the Bosnian town of Gorazde as "correct and 
necessary." The Western community thus demonstrates that it is 
not prepared to accept the "Bosnian Serbs' continual violations 
of international law," Kinkel said in Bonn today. At the same 
time, the Western community said it was not prepared to accept 
developments like those in Gorazde in other parts of Bosnia. 
  It is necessary, "alongside the military measures," to get 
the negotiating process into motion again, said Kinkel. The 
United Nations, the European Union, the United States, and 
Russia were jointly called upon to take a fresh initiative to 
get the warring parties to the negotiating table. 

</TEXT>

