<H3> <TI>   Daily Sees Bosnia as `Touchstone' for Clinton </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Sees Bosnia as `Touchstone' for Clinton </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2404144094 Vienna KURIER in German 23 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2404144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by "Rau.": "Will to Leadership"] </F>
  [Text] NATO has decided after all in favor of an ultimatum 
to the Serbs to leave Gorazde and the other "protection zones" 
or else Serbian positions will be bombed. U.S. President Bill 
Clinton seems to have finally brought himself to push this 
through NATO. 
  No matter how much Bill Clinton rejects this, Bosnia is 
becoming a touchstone for his leadership abilities. The 
situation in the former Yugoslavia is extremely complicated and 
risky. However, it is the job of the U.S. President to take 
resolute action and risks if necessary. 
  The Clinton Administration has given way to local chiefs of 
bandits in Haiti and Somalia. If it does not cope with the 
Bosnian Serbs -- even if it were to withdraw while giving 
weapons to the Muslims -- the judgment on its competence will be 
passed. 

</TEXT>

