<H3> <TI>   Institute Says Country Escaped Recession Lightly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Institute Says Country Escaped Recession Lightly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2104133294 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 21 Apr 94 p 15 </F>
<F P=103> AU2104133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Mild Recession in Austria"] </F>
  [Text] Vienna -- Austria overcame the international 
recession in 1993 more effectively than neighboring countries, 
the Economic Research Institute (Wifo) reported yesterday. At 
0.3 percent, GNP dropped much less than that of western Germany 
(1.9 percent). 
  Austrian industry reacted quickly to the declining orders 
from abroad. It reduced production by 3 percent and investments 
by one-fifth. A total of 6.5 percent of all jobs were lost in 
industry in 1993. Consumption and the construction industry had 
a stabilizing effect. 
  The recession left clear traces in the budget, however: At 
98 billion schillings, the budget deficit was twice as high as 
planned. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

