<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Get out of Gorazde! NATO has once again given 
an ultimatum to the Serbs. [passage omitted] Listen to the 
reaction of Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, who was in Nancy 
yesterday, speaking to Olivier Schneid: 
  [Begin recording] [Juppe] Last night's decisions by the UN 
Security Council following the French initiative asking the 
Serbs to withdraw from Gorazde, should be followed by actions. 
When persuasion fails, force should be used. I think, 
therefore, it is logical that NATO should provide the United 
Nations with the means it requested in order to enforce 
international law. I would also like to say that we should not 
reduce our diplomatic efforts. 
