<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Meets Belgian Counterpart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Meets Belgian Counterpart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104144394 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1400 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgian troops will not take part in any more UN 
peacekeeping forces for several months at least. This was 
announced by Leo Delcroix, the Belgian defense minister, who met 
his French counterpart Francois Leotard in Paris today. 
  "If we are called upon for new missions, I think we will 
abstain for a certain period of time. We need several months to 
recover from the events." The minister was certainly referring 
to the death of ten Belgian UN peacekeepers in Rwanda. 
  Leo Delcroix said he would reexamine the situation in the 
autumn, but, he said, Belgium will not withdraw from missions 
currently underway, in particular in ex-Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

