  [Text] Stuttgart (DPA) -- PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat will 
visit Stuttgart on 2 May (Monday) at the invitation of Edzard 
Reuter, chairman of the board of directors of Daimler-Benz AG. 
According to an announcement made by the corporation on Friday 
[22 April], talks with the board of directors are scheduled. 
The Baden-Wuerttemberg land government confirmed that Minister 
President Erwin Teufel (Christian Democratic Union) plans to 
receive the PLO chairman for an exchange of views on the peace 
process in the Middle East. 
  Since Reuter's visit to Israel in September 1992, 
Daimler-Benz has been intensively working on expanding economic 
relations with the entire Middle East region. At the beginning 
of the year Daimler opened a representation in Tel Aviv and a 
liaison office in the Egyptian capital of Cairo. 

