  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- On Monday [25 April] a development 
aid agreement with financial promises of up to 50 million German 
marks was signed in Bonn by FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
(Free Democratic Party of Germany) and his Bolivian counterpart, 
Antonio Aranibar Quiroga. Kinkel encouraged the foreign 
minister to press for more private German investment during his 
contacts with business representatives in Germany. Aranibar is 
in Germany for a three-day visit. On Monday he was also the 
guest of the Ibero America Association and of the 
Friedrich-Ebert Foundation, which is affiliated to the Social 
Democratic Party of Germany. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

