  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, April 23 -- The defense of Italian farm 
products will be one of the battle cries of Forza Italia during 
the campaign for European [Parliament--EP] elections in June. 
Forza Italia leader Silvio Berlusconi and his aides discussed 
the matter at a meeting today and next week will also draft 
administrative matters. 
  The protection of Italian farm products both at home and on 
European markets means defending job levels in Italy, according 
to Forza Italia spokesman Antonio Tajani. He claimed that 
production in this important sector of the economy has been 
buffeted, above all, by an invasion of South American farm 
products. 

