<F P=106> [Article signed JQ/RP: "Ciba To Create Joint Venture in </F>
China"] 
  [Text] Basel, 21 Apr (ATS) -- The Swiss 
chemical-pharmaceutical group Ciba has decided to set up a joint 
venture in China. Two months after it established a branch in 
that country, Ciba's Plants Protection Division signed an 
agreement with the Qingdao Pesticides Factory in Qingdao on 
Thursday [21 April], the Basel-based chemical group said. The 
new company will produce active substances as well as compounds. 
  The Chinese partner will hold 45 percent of the assets, the 
other 55 percent being the property of Ciba, which also will 
designate the director. The new company, which will start its 
activities in 1996 once its production units have been 
completed, will employ around 180 people. 

