<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry on Repatriation of Troops From Kenya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604094694 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 0900 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Eighty paracommandos are landing at Melsbroek 
military airport outside Brussels this morning. They left from 
Nairobi in Kenya last night, following the evacuation operation 
of Belgians and other Westerners from Rwanda nearly three weeks 
ago. Several hundreds of Belgian troops are still stationed at 
the military camp at the Nairobi airport. The Defense Ministry 
in Brussels says they will all be repatriated. Earlier it was 
expected that the troops would stay in Nairobi to intervene if 
necessary in Burundi, south of Rwanda where ethnic violence has 
claimed thousands of lives in the past few months. [passage 
