<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Last Major Russian Division Leaves Saxony-Anhalt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Last Major Russian Division Leaves Saxony-Anhalt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204162594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1245 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2204162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Burg (DDP/ADN) -- Today the 10th Russian Guards 
Tank Division left Altengrabow Garrison in Burg district. This 
means that the last major combat unit of the former Soviet 
forces in Saxony-Anhalt is now on its way home. 
  Wolfgang Rauls, deputy prime minister and land environment 
minister, stressed that there has been extensive personal 
contacts between local people and the members of the division, 
despite the odd problem with living side by side over the past 
few years. [passage omitted] 
  Before the withdrawal agreement there were around 100,000 
Russian soldiers as well as 40,000 civilian employees and family 
members stationed in Saxony-Anhalt. They were based at a total 
of 276 locations. 

</TEXT>

