<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Stresses Need To Help South Africa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Stresses Need To Help South Africa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504140094 Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG in German 24 Apr 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> AU2504140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel: "We Help </F>
South Africa"] 
  [Text] For the first time in South Africa's history, all 
citizens, no matter what the color of their skin is, will elect 
a joint government this week. The horrible apartheid system 
will finally be buried this April 1994. 
  Germany helped to prepare the elections. In these days, 100 
German election observers are at the Cape. For years, we have 
supported antiapartheid organizations -- with almost 500 million 
German marks since 1975. At the same time, we always held a 
critical dialogue with the South African Government. This 
farsighted policy of the Federal Government is now bearing fruit. 
  In early September I will extend invitations to a conference 
in Berlin for promotion of the economy in southern Africa. 
Together with our partners in the European Union, we must and 
will support South Africa now with a comprehensive relief 
program in the difficult transition period. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

