<F P=106> ["vwd." report: "Again Major Development Aid for India"] </F>
  [Text] Bonn -- Within the framework of bilateral 
development cooperation with India, the Federal Government has 
now promised the country 315 billion German marks [DM] for 
financial cooperation and DM36.5 billion for technical 
cooperation. The FRG Government is increasingly concentrating 
its development policy cooperation with India on programs to 
combat poverty and for environmental protection. 

